text: It was my first visit and I was told to eat after the service and then go, so I waited and I felt bad when they made me do this and that. Does a church force a first-time visitor to do this or that with their fingers? I don't care if you sign up and serve at a place you frequent, but I don't think it's a good idea to force church work like that on someone who went to see the atmosphere on the first day.

thank you
Gracious worship & a really delicious, simple Korean meal that you can’t find in Singapore👍🏻👍🏻
It was a truly grateful time.
We sincerely congratulate you on your 10th anniversary.
Thank you so much for the gracious worship and delicious meal. We sincerely congratulate you on your 10th anniversary~♡
